
[1]diastoly

   DIASTOLE, DIASTOLY, n. [Gr., to set or send from.]

   1. Among physicians, a dilation of the heart, auricles and arteries;
   opposed to systole or contraction.

   2. In grammar, the extension of a syllable; or a figure by which a
   syllable naturally short is made long.
